                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/22468: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-27T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 27, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. Your 211, June 25, 4 p.m. You may deliver the following message to President
                    Barclay from President Roosevelt: <pb facs="0396" n="384" xml:id="pg_384"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I am gratified at the signing of an agreement which binds our two
                            countries together in the common purpose of resisting the forces of
                            aggression. As a practical matter, I hope that for the present no
                            publicity will be given to Liberia’s courageous action.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
